pub.citation: Samuel, R. et al. 2005. MOLECULAR PHYLOGENETICS OF PHYLLANTHACEAE: EVIDENCE FROM PLASTID MATK AND NUCLEAR PHYC SEQUENCES. American Journal of Botany 92(1): 132-141.

pmmd.notes: One of the six most parsimonious trees of the combined analysis of matK and PHYC (length 5 3440, CI 5 0.59, RI 5 0.75). Branch lengths (DELTRAN optimization) and bootstrap percentages (.50) are indicated above and below the branches, respectively. Arrowheads indicate nodes not present in the strict consensus tree.
